<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="positive-adj">positive <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'pɒzətɪv/    美 /'pɑːzətɪv/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>正面的；积极乐观的；有益的</strong></h4>
<p>反 negative： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I believe that the Internet has <strong>positive effects</strong> on our lives. 
我认为互联网对我们的生活有正面的影响。</p><footer>译林⑦ – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>People with high EQs usually have <strong>positive attitudes</strong> towards life. 
高情商的人往往有着积极的生活态度。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>确实的；确信的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a positive fact 
确信无疑的事实</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She was quite <strong>positive about</strong> the amount of money involved. 
她对所涉及的钱数十分肯定。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I am positive that I gave you his address. 
我肯定把他的地址给你了。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>正的；阳性的</strong></h4>
<p>反 negative： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a positive number 
正数</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Anyone, once <strong>tested positive</strong> for the bird flu virus, will receive free medical treatment from our government.
任何人一旦被检测出禽流感病毒呈阳性，将获得政府提供的免费医疗。</p><footer>2013 福建改</footer></div></div>